<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 03 at 6:59PM EDT until May 03 at 7:15PM EDT by NWS Wilmington</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 715 PM EDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN BLADEN AND NORTHEASTERN ROBESON COUNTIES...
At 658 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Duart, or 15
miles northeast of Lumberton, moving east at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to vehicles is possible.
Locations impacted include...
St. Pauls, Tobermory, Howellsville, Tolarsville, Duart and Tar Heel.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
